{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894/comments/26385403.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894#comment-26385403"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 1894, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add hint text to Search field in Palette"}, "content": {"raw": "Unfortunately there is no SIGNAL click or focus for the QLineEdit (Search Field), hence the text cannot dissapear when the user clicks into the text field.\n\nNow there are two possible solutions:\n\n1. subclass QLineEdit and generate our own type, where a mouse click signal or focus signal on the text field is implemented.\n\n2. User another SIGNAL of QLineEdit, for example when the user starts typing in text field the text disappears. \n\nCurrently the last edit remains inside the text field throughout the use of the plotting utility. Do you want the hint text to appear again when user clicks somewhere else and search is done?\n\nFurthermore if the user enters the Search Tab the focus is automatically given to the search field, so the text would immediately disappear. Perhaps if you want the text to remain a hint is not that useful (I found this post :D http://www.uxmatters.com/mt/archives/2010/03/dont-put-hints-inside-text-boxes-in-web-forms.php). \n\nHowever, the implementation is ready you just have to tell me if you prefer implementation 1 or 2.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Unfortunately there is no SIGNAL click or focus for the QLineEdit (Search Field), hence the text cannot dissapear when the user clicks into the text field.</p>\n<p>Now there are two possible solutions:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>subclass QLineEdit and generate our own type, where a mouse click signal or focus signal on the text field is implemented.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>User another SIGNAL of QLineEdit, for example when the user starts typing in text field the text disappears. </p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Currently the last edit remains inside the text field throughout the use of the plotting utility. Do you want the hint text to appear again when user clicks somewhere else and search is done?</p>\n<p>Furthermore if the user enters the Search Tab the focus is automatically given to the search field, so the text would immediately disappear. Perhaps if you want the text to remain a hint is not that useful (I found this post :D <a href=\"http://www.uxmatters.com/mt/archives/2010/03/dont-put-hints-inside-text-boxes-in-web-forms.php\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">http://www.uxmatters.com/mt/archives/2010/03/dont-put-hints-inside-text-boxes-in-web-forms.php</a>). </p>\n<p>However, the implementation is ready you just have to tell me if you prefer implementation 1 or 2.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-03-21T14:16:02.481958+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "almin causevic", "uuid": "{742c4b94-517d-4121-b9d4-4db5d7d196d2}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B742c4b94-517d-4121-b9d4-4db5d7d196d2%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B742c4b94-517d-4121-b9d4-4db5d7d196d2%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e11efa4c0b999aca807842d66278f48bd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsAC-1.png"}}, "nickname": "almin", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:294af8d9-ad1d-4a75-bb9f-33404bfbb24c"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 26385403}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894/comments/26393898.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894#comment-26393898"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 1894, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add hint text to Search field in Palette"}, "content": {"raw": "@almin , have you tried playing with [`QLineEdit::placeholderText`](http://doc.qt.io/qt-4.8/qlineedit.html#placeholderText-prop)? It might end up not being customizable enough for what we want here, but maybe it is the easiest solution.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>@almin , have you tried playing with <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://doc.qt.io/qt-4.8/qlineedit.html#placeholderText-prop\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>QLineEdit::placeholderText</code></a>? It might end up not being customizable enough for what we want here, but maybe it is the easiest solution.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-03-21T18:59:49.166178+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 26393898}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894/comments/26395102.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894#comment-26395102"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 1894, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add hint text to Search field in Palette"}, "content": {"raw": "I'm not sure what the best technical approach is, but here is the suggested behavior:\n\n* Hint text appears by default\n* Clicking into text field clears help text. Or, help text disappears when user starts typing.** \n* When user clicks out of text field, search query remains.\n* If user deletes search query, help text reappears.\n\n** One thing I want to avoid is the following annoying behavior I've seen in a few places: User clicks into a text field with help text. User starts typing, but help text doesn't clear, resulting in the search query appearing in the middle of the help text.\n\nDoes that make sense?\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I'm not sure what the best technical approach is, but here is the suggested behavior:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Hint text appears by default</li>\n<li>Clicking into text field clears help text. Or, help text disappears when user starts typing.** </li>\n<li>When user clicks out of text field, search query remains.</li>\n<li>If user deletes search query, help text reappears.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>** One thing I want to avoid is the following annoying behavior I've seen in a few places: User clicks into a text field with help text. User starts typing, but help text doesn't clear, resulting in the search query appearing in the middle of the help text.</p>\n<p>Does that make sense?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-03-21T19:55:59.762825+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steffi Paepcke", "uuid": "{88ec2edf-5653-4e93-b139-6f2418d9fde5}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B88ec2edf-5653-4e93-b139-6f2418d9fde5%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B88ec2edf-5653-4e93-b139-6f2418d9fde5%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/account/spaepcke/avatar/"}}, "nickname": "spaepcke", "type": "user", "account_id": null}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 26395102}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894/comments/26508030.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894#comment-26508030"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 1894, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add hint text to Search field in Palette"}, "content": {"raw": "Yes sure. Thank you Louise for the suggestion. With QLineEdit::placeholderText it is easy to achieve the suggested behaviour by Steffi (text disappears on click, search query remains on delete the help text reappears).\n\nHowever, when a user clicks the first time on the search tab, the focus is given to the search text field, so there is no hint text. Should I rermove the first focus, so the hint text appears immediately on first search tab click?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Yes sure. Thank you Louise for the suggestion. With QLineEdit::placeholderText it is easy to achieve the suggested behaviour by Steffi (text disappears on click, search query remains on delete the help text reappears).</p>\n<p>However, when a user clicks the first time on the search tab, the focus is given to the search text field, so there is no hint text. Should I rermove the first focus, so the hint text appears immediately on first search tab click?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-03-26T00:28:04.721739+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "almin causevic", "uuid": "{742c4b94-517d-4121-b9d4-4db5d7d196d2}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B742c4b94-517d-4121-b9d4-4db5d7d196d2%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B742c4b94-517d-4121-b9d4-4db5d7d196d2%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e11efa4c0b999aca807842d66278f48bd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsAC-1.png"}}, "nickname": "almin", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:294af8d9-ad1d-4a75-bb9f-33404bfbb24c"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 26508030}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894/comments/26508114.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894#comment-26508114"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 1894, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add hint text to Search field in Palette"}, "content": {"raw": "Ah, I see the issue. In this case, I think it's better to leave the focus in the search field and just not have the hint text unless the user deletes the search query and clicks out of the field. I suspect that users would prefer the faster interaction of clicking on the Search tab and immediately being able to type their query, without having to first click into the field. ", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Ah, I see the issue. In this case, I think it's better to leave the focus in the search field and just not have the hint text unless the user deletes the search query and clicks out of the field. I suspect that users would prefer the faster interaction of clicking on the Search tab and immediately being able to type their query, without having to first click into the field. </p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-03-26T00:46:25.592759+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steffi Paepcke", "uuid": "{88ec2edf-5653-4e93-b139-6f2418d9fde5}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B88ec2edf-5653-4e93-b139-6f2418d9fde5%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B88ec2edf-5653-4e93-b139-6f2418d9fde5%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/account/spaepcke/avatar/"}}, "nickname": "spaepcke", "type": "user", "account_id": null}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 26508114}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894/comments/26508483.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894#comment-26508483"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 1894, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add hint text to Search field in Palette"}, "content": {"raw": "Done `plotting`", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Done <code>plotting</code></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-03-26T02:02:35.630765+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "almin causevic", "uuid": "{742c4b94-517d-4121-b9d4-4db5d7d196d2}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B742c4b94-517d-4121-b9d4-4db5d7d196d2%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B742c4b94-517d-4121-b9d4-4db5d7d196d2%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e11efa4c0b999aca807842d66278f48bd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsAC-1.png"}}, "nickname": "almin", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:294af8d9-ad1d-4a75-bb9f-33404bfbb24c"}, "updated_on": "2016-03-26T02:03:42.376356+00:00", "type": "issue_comment", "id": 26508483}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894/comments/26530788.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894#comment-26530788"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 1894, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add hint text to Search field in Palette"}, "content": {"raw": "pull request #2214", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p><a href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2214/added-hint-text-to-search-field-in-palette\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">pull request #2214</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-03-28T03:55:48.680248+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 26530788}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1894/comments/26543728.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gaze